-- Chelsea Football Club Extends Frank Lampard’s Contract by a Year
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2013-05-16T12:00:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-16/chelsea-football-club-extends-frank-lampard-s-contract-by-a-year.html
Chelsea Football Club extended its
contract with player and club top scorer  Frank Lampard  by one
year, it said on its website.  “Frank has been an important player for Chelsea Football
Club for a long time and has played a significant part in the
club’s success,” the club’s Chief Executive Ron Gourlay said in
a statement. The extension will keep Lampard tied to the club
until 2014.  “I’m absolutely delighted,” Lampard, 35, said.
“Everybody knows I always maintained the dream was to stay at
Chelsea. We’ve been talking for ages and even though it went on
for quite a period it was always amicable.”  The London club is owned by Russian billionaire  Roman
Abramovich .  Lampard joined Chelsea in 2001 from West Ham.  To contact the reporter on this story:
